<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870604-0048 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Burlington Industries Inc.</HL><DD> 06/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BUR MSTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)TEXTILES AND APPAREL (TEX) </IN><TEXT>   BURLINGTON INDUSTRIES INC.: A group led by Morgan Stanley Group Inc. said it received commitments for the financing of its $76-a-share, or $2.07 billion, bid for the Greensboro, N.C.-based textile concern. The group said a syndicate of banks made commitments for the remaining $350 million in bank financing for the leveraged buyout. The company previously announced commitments from three banks to provide $1.5 billion of the $1.85 billion bank credit. In addition, Morgan, Equitable Capital Management Corp. and others have committed to provide $861 million in bridge financing and equity capital. </TEXT></DOC>